# Database Design & SQL

## Core Concepts
- Entities and attributes
- Primary and foreign keys
- Relationships (1:1, 1:M, M:M)
- Normalization (1NF, 2NF, 3NF)

## SQL Skills
- SELECT, WHERE, JOIN, GROUP BY
- Data filtering and aggregation

## ERD (Entity Relationship Diagram)
Used to visually design database structure.

## Why It Matters
Good database design ensures:
- Data integrity
- Reduced redundancy
- Efficient queries

## Real-World Use
Used in business systems, applications, and data storage solutions.
